
Functional Requirements
Functional requirements describe what the system does.
•	The KAUESSEN system shall display the daily food items and their prices to the customer. 
•	The customer shall be able to choose a specific pickup time between 08:00 and 16:00. 
•	The KAUESSEN system shall handle the payment using the student ID balance or a credit card. 
•	The KAUESSEN system shall generate a unique 6-digit tracking number for each order. 
•	The KAUESSEN system shall sort the active orders on the staff dashboard in chronological order by pickup time. 

Non-Functional Requirements
Non-functional requirements define the system constraints. These requirements should be measurable and quantifiable.
•	The KAUESSEN system shall load the daily menu page within 2 seconds on a standard 4G network. 
•	The system should support up to 500 concurrent users without system failure. 
•	The system should maintain 99% uptime during university hours (07:00–17:00). 
•	The system should encrypt all customer payment data. 
•	The system should perform daily database backups at 23:00. 
